    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-07-12T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-07-12T03:00:00-05:00" n="729"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/7–1252: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Pakistan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PGW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d729fn1">This telegram was repeated to New Delhi, London,
                        and New York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-07-12T13:00:00+05:00"
                            >July 12, 1952—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. Be Delhi’s 155 of July 11 to <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>. <gloss
                        target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> requested me call on him this A.M. and
                    asked for news from Delhi re Kashmir. I informed him <gloss target="#t_Amb1"
                        >Amb</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BCB1">Bowles</persName> had had second conversation with
                        <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> in which latter stated there had
                    been no change in his own position, and that he felt any further discussions
                    shld come thru <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> in NY. <persName
                        corresp="#p_NK1">Nazimuddin</persName> said he was deeply disappointed
                    because “I really think I made <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> a
                    very sporting offer.”</p>
                <p>I have also talked to <persName corresp="#p_KCSM1">Zafrulla</persName> on subj,
                    at his request. He said he had yesterday recd a “most disturbing” <gloss
                        target="#t_msg1">msg</gloss> from <persName corresp="#p_BAS1"
                        >Bokhari</persName> who quoted <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName>
                    to the effect he had been preparing to present concrete proposals of his own re
                    troop question and induction of pleb administrator <pb facs="0230" n="1280"
                        xml:id="pg_1280"/> into office, when “negots” were undertaken in the
                    subcontinent which “short circuited” him and made it impossible for him to
                    proceed.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KCSM1">Zafrulla</persName> said he hoped <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> wld clear up <persName corresp="#p_GDF1"
                        >Graham</persName>’s misconceptions concerning the informal “explorations”
                    which have been in progress in Delhi and Karachi and explain to him the
                    circumstances in which they had been undertaken. He also hoped the US wld urge
                        <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> to “get on with it” now that
                        <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> had clearly turned down the
                        <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> proposal and to present his own
                    “concrete proposals to the two parties without delay”. If both parties accepted
                        <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> proposals, the <gloss
                        target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> said, negots cld go on from there. If
                    either party rejected them, <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> wld
                    then have to report failure to <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PGW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
